Description: Kernel-based hypothesis tests for causal inference and
    distributional treatment effects. Implements backdoor-adjusted HSIC
    (bd-HSIC) for testing causal association, and doubly robust kernel
    statistics (DR-DATE, DR-DETT) for testing distributional treatment
    effects beyond mean shifts. Supports binary, continuous, and mixed
    treatments, hierarchical/nested data structures, and scales to large
    datasets via Nystrom approximation and random Fourier features.
